+ * `reckoner.tick` — periodic Reckoner tick relay.
+ *
+ * The Reckoner contributes this relay through its apparatus
+ * `supportKit.relays` slot, paired with a kit-contributed standing
+ * order at `@every 60s` so any guild that installs the Reckoner
+ * alongside the Clockworks gets the tick wired automatically.
+ *
+ * The tick is the **only** path that drives scheduler evaluation in
+ * the Reckoner — there is no CDC observer, no startup catch-up scan,
+ * and no per-writ-update entry into evaluation. Each fire builds one
+ * `SchedulerInput` for the entire candidate set so the active
+ * scheduler sees every held petition at once (the global-view shape
+ * the priority-walk and capacity-aware schedulers need).
+ *
+ * Per-fire sequence (see commission brief):
+ *
+ *   1. Fail-loud guard — if the active scheduler reference has not
+ *      been resolved yet (pre-seal tick during a startup race) throw
+ *      so test fixtures get a deterministic loud signal. Production
+ *      never trips this; the standing-order schedule is bound after
+ *      `phase:started` fires.
+ *   2. Re-read + validate `reckoner.schedulerConfig` (D17/D18). On
+ *      `validateConfig` throw, log fail-loud and skip the tick — no
+ *      rows, no transitions.
+ *   3. Query held petitions (writs in `new` carrying `ext.reckoner`)
+ *      using the same find-by-phase shape the previous catch-up scan
+ *      used.
+ *   4. Apply source/disabled gates inline. Disabled-source petitions
